| rev9Score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name="Slant">{{cite web|url=http://www.slantmagazine.com/music/review/sia-1000-forms-of-fear |title=Sia: 1000 Forms of Fear {{!}} Album Review |publisher=[[Slant Magazine]] |first=Annie |last=Galvin |date=6 July 2014 |accessdate=12 July 2014}}</ref>
| rev10 = ''[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]''
| rev10Score = 8/10<ref name="Spin">{{cite web|url=http://www.spin.com/reviews/sia-1000-forms-of-fear/ |title=Prolific Hitmaker Sia Reclaims the Spotlight on '1000 Forms of Fear' |work=[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]] |first=Maura |last=Johnston |date=7 July 2014 |accessdate=12 July 2014}}</ref>
}}
''1000 Forms of Fear'' received mostly positive reviews from [[music journalism|music critics]]. At [[Metacritic]], which assigns a [[standard score|normalised]] rating out of 100 to reviews from mainstream critics, the album received an [[weighted mean|average score]] of 76, based on 28 reviews.<ref name="Metacritic"/> ''[[The Boston Globe]]'' critic Sarah Rodman described the release as "dynamite,"<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.bostonglobe.com/arts/music/2014/07/07/sia-forms-fear/9e2TGfXsvWUBphw7ikqSiO/story.html|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6WSIZ58ZC|title=Sia: '1000 Forms of Fear'|work=[[The Boston Globe]]|date=7 July 2014|archivedate=19 February 2015|first=Sarah|last=Rodman}}</ref> while Heather Phares from [[AllMusic]] called the album "the sound of [Sia] owning her success."<ref name="AllMusic"/> Writing for ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]'', Helen Brown praised the album's production and "inspirational" lyrics showcasing Sia struggling to deal with [[drug addiction]] and [[bipolar disorder]].<ref name="Telegraph"/> ''[[Rolling Stone]]''{{'}}s Julianne Escobedo Shepherd simply wrote that "she sounds like a superstar;"<ref name="RS"/> while Maura Johnston of ''[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]'' characterised ''1000 Forms of Fear'' as "a chunk of the human emotional spectrum committed to record."<ref name="Spin"/> On behalf of ''[[The New York Times]]'', Jon Pareles lauded the "loopy, unresolved passions" on the album in favour of "the triumphal, laminated, computer-perfected tone of Sia<U+2019>s clients."<ref name="NYTimes"/>

Writing for [[Slant Magazine]], Annie Galvin opined that ''1000 Forms of Fear'' "should be the vessel that rockets the singer out of relative obscurity and into the stratosphere populated by those more recognizable stars who've come to dominate the pop-music universe thanks, in part, to her songwriting skills."<ref name="Slant"/> Mikael Wood writing for the ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' praised Sia's vocals and the production held by [[Greg Kurstin]].<ref name="LATimes"/> Likewise, ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]''{{'}}s Adam Markovitz positively viewed Sia's voice as "astonishing," giving the album a B score.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2014/08/26/1000-forms-fear|title=1000 Forms of Fear|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|first=Adam |last=Markovitz|date=26 August 2014|accessdate=19 February 2015}}</ref> On a less enthusiastic review, ''[[The Guardian]]'' Harriet Gibsone shared that the album was so impeccable and "contemporary-sounding" that "its impact may fade with time."<ref name="Guardian"/> ''[[The A.V. Club]]'' writer Annie Zaleski wrote: "''1000 Forms of Fear'' certainly has the songs and contemporary sheen to make Sia a star in her own right, but it's at the expense of both her emotional intimacy and her offbeat personality."<ref name="AVClub"/>

===Accolades===
Sarah Rodman of ''The Boston Globe'' labelled ''1000 Forms of Fear'' the "Best Surprise" of 2014.<ref name="BostonGlobe">{{cite web|url=http://www.bostonglobe.com/arts/music/2014/12/13/best-albums/a8YrRcfhHAmUNXt8WCbhDK/story.html|title=Sarah Rodman<U+2019>s 2014 best albums picks|first=Sarah|last=Rodman|date=13 December 2014|work=The Boston Globe|accessdate=17 December 2014}}</ref> It ranked number 13 on [[Digital Spy]]'s list of Top 15 Albums of 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/feature/a614406/what-is-digital-spys-album-of-the-year-2014-we-reveal-our-top-15.html#~oXNcxv6hrDpwJk|title=Digital Spy's Top Albums Of 2014|date=6 December 2014|work={{noitalic|[[Digital Spy]]}}|accessdate=12 December 2014}}</ref> Jon Pareles from ''The New York Times'' placed the album at number 5 on his list of favourite albums of the year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2014/12/14/arts/music/jon-pareless-favorite-albums-of-2014.html|title=Jon Pareles<U+2019>s Favorite Albums and Songs of 2014|work=[[The New York Times]]|first=Jon|last=Pareles|authorlink=Jon Pareles|date=11 December 2014|accessdate=17 December 2014}}</ref> It also appeared on the lists of the best albums of 2014 of Slant Magazine (number 13<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.slantmagazine.com/features/article/the-25-best-albums-of-2014/P3|first=Sal|last=Cinquemani|title=Th 25 Best Albums of 2014 (page 3)|publisher=Slant Magazine|date=11 December 2014|accessdate=17 December 2014}}</ref>) and ''The Daily Telegraph'' (number 44<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/music/cdreviews/11252866/best-albums-of-2014.html|title=Best albums of 2014|work=[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]]|date=27 November 2014|accessdate=19 December 2014}}</ref>). ''Rolling Stone'' ranked it number 20 on its list of 20 Best Pop Albums of 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rollingstone.com/music/lists/20-best-pop-albums-of-2014-20141219/sia-1000-forms-of-fear-20141217|title=20 Best Pop Albums of 2014|work=Rolling Stone|accessdate=21 February 2015}}</ref> At the [[ARIA Music Awards of 2014]], Sia won [[ARIA Award for Album of the Year|Album of the Year]], [[ARIA Award for Best Female Artist|Best Female Artist]] and [[ARIA Award for Best Pop Release|Best Pop Release]] for ''1000 Forms of Fear''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.couriermail.com.au/entertainment/confidential/brisbane-band-sheppard-win-best-group-at-aria-awards/story-fnn7l51k-1227136216324|title=Brisbane band Sheppard win Best Group at ARIA Awards|date=27 November 2014|first=Noel|last=Mengel|work=[[The Courier-Mail]]|accessdate=20 February 2015}}</ref> The lead single "Chandelier" received four [[Grammy Award|Grammy]] nominations for [[Grammy Award for Song of the Year|Song of the Year]], [[Grammy Award for Record of the Year|Record of the Year]], [[Grammy Award for Best Pop Solo Performance|Best Pop Solo Performance]] and [[Grammy Award for Best Music Video|Best Music Video]] at the [[57th Grammy Awards]].<ref name="Spin Grammys">{{cite web|url=http://www.spin.com/articles/grammys-2015-nominees-beyonce-sam-smith-iggy-azalea/ |title=Grammys 2015 Nominees: Sam Smith, HAIM, Iggy Azalea, and More |work=[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]] |first=James |last=Grebey |date=5 December 2014 |accessdate=5 December 2014}}</ref>

==Commercial performance==
''1000 Forms of Fear'' debuted at number one on the US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] with first-week sales of 52,000 copies. By doing so, it became the lowest sales figure for a number-one album on the chart in nearly two years.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6157709/sia-1000-forms-of-fear-billboard-200-soundscan-chandelier|title=Sia Earns First No. 1 Album On Billboard 200 with '1000 Forms of Fear'|work=Billboard|date=16 July 2014|first=Keith|last=Caulfield|accessdate=20 February 2015}}</ref> ''The Guardian''{{'}}s Clem Bastow commented on the album's success in the US: "Australian artists typically fare better in the Billboard Hot 100 singles chart, but even then, Furler finds herself in rarefied company."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theguardian.com/music/australia-culture-blog/2014/jul/17/sia-1000-forms-of-fear-no-1-us-album|title=Sia's 1000 Forms Of Fear debuts at No 1 in US album charts|date=17 July 2014|first=Clem|last=Bastown|work=The Guardian|accessdate=20 February 2015}}</ref> On behalf of ''[[The Sydney Morning Herald]]'', George Palathingal opined that the album's debuting atop the ''Billboard'' 100 is the result of "a stroke of (anti-)marketing genius" and "a case of quality pop music standing proud."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.smh.com.au/entertainment/music/sia-furlers-1000-forms-of-fear-goes-no1-in-us-albums-chart-20140717-ztw49.html|title=Sia Furler's 1000 Forms of Fear goes No.1 in US albums chart|date=17 July 2014|first=George|last=Palathingal|work=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]]|accessdate=20 February 2015}}</ref> As of January 2015, ''1000 Forms of Fear'' has sold 177,000 copies in the United States, according to [[Nielsen SoundScan]].<ref name="us_sales">{{cite news|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6443523/hot-100-chart-moves-sia-video-controversy|title=Hot 100 Chart Moves: Video Controversy Sends Sia's 'Elastic Heart' to No. 17 Debut|first=Gary|last=Trust|work=Billboard|date=16 January 2015|accessdate=18 January 2015}}</ref>

In Australia, the release debuted atop the [[ARIA Charts|ARIA Albums Chart]] on 20 July 2014 and remained on the chart for 20 weeks.<ref name="aus"/> The album was [[List of music recording certifications|certified]] gold by the [[Australian Recording Industry Association]] for having shipped 35,000 units in the country.<ref name="ARIA2014">{{cite web|url=http://ariacharts.com.au/chart/albums |title= ARIA Albums Chart |publisher=Australian Recording Industry Association|date=1 September 2014|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20140906185517/http://www.ariacharts.com.au/chart/albums|archivedate=6 September 2014}}</ref> ''1000 Forms of Fear'' also peaked at number one on the [[Canadian Albums Chart]].<ref name="va"/> The release also charted within the top five [[record chart|albums chart]]s of several countries, including Norway (number 2), New Zealand, Sweden and Switzerland (number 4) and Denmark (number 5).<ref name="aus"/> In the United Kingdom, ''1000 Forms of Fear'' peaked at number 11 on the [[UK Albums Chart]] and was certified silver by the [[British Phonographic Industry]].<ref name="gbr"/><ref name="BPI">{{cite web|url=http://www.bpi.co.uk/certified-awards.aspx|title=Certified Awards Search|publisher=British Phonographic Industry|accessdate=31 January 2015}}</ref>

